title: Navigate forwards to a tab list in reading mode
task: Navigate forwards to a tab list
setupScriptDescription: sets focus on a link before the tab list
instructions: With the reading cursor on the 'Navigate forwards from here' link, Navigate to the 'Danish Composers' tab list.
assertion2: Name of the tab list, 'Danish Composers', is conveyed
assertion3: Role of the selected item, 'tab', is conveyed
assertion4: Name of the focused tab, 'Maria Ahlefeldt', is conveyed
assertion5: State of the focused tab, 'selected', is conveyed
assertion6: Position of the focused tab, 1, is conveyed
assertion7: Number of tabs in the tab list, 4, is conveyed

title: Navigate forwards to a tab panel in interaction mode
task: Navigate forwards to a tab panel
setupScriptDescription: sets focus on the first tab
instructions: With focus on the 'Maria Ahlefeldt' tab, navigate to the tab panel.",
assertion3: Textual content of the tab panel is conveyed as 'Maria Theresia Ahlefeldt (16 January 1755 – 20 December 1810) was a Danish, (originally German), composer. She is known as the first female composer in Denmark. Maria Theresia composed music for several ballets, operas, and plays of the royal theatre. She was given good critic as a composer and described as a “virkelig Tonekunstnerinde” ('a True Artist of Music').'
